c_code": 48409, "sorries": 38}, {"sha": "236271099fa92895d63442d110419c4845c42e8b", "short_sha": "23627109", "date": "2026-07-05T15:20:43+09:00", "subject": "workspace[0013 r5] ground: integrate 0011-ground", "lean_files": 90, "loc": 84203, "loc_code": 48410, "sorries": 38}, {"sha": "0fb724352dd52a3d65e2cee20540ab759b9d2c56", "short_sha": "0fb72435", "date": "2026-07-05T16:15:55+09:00", "subject": "Grassmannian representability (thm:grassmannian_representable): corrected the statement to the [Nitsure] hypotheses \u2014 V locally free of rank r, 1 \u2264 d \u2264 r (the old skeleton over an arbitrary sheaf of modules was not the cited theorem and not known to be true) \u2014 and proved it modulo two clean leaves. New GrassmannianRepresentability.lean: the trivialised case Grass(V,d) \u2245 Grass(r,d) is representable by S \u2a2f Gr(d,r) via the forget \u22a3 star adjunction and the merged absolute chart construction (axiom-clean); the restriction comparison (Over.map j)^* Grass(V,d) \u2245 Grass(j^*V, d) is proved from the pullback pseudofunctor coherences; the final theorem descends along a trivialising cover. Remaining typed-sorry leaves: Zariski descent of representability (EGA 0_I 4.5.4) and the Zariski sheaf axiom for the Grassmannian functor. Blueprint gains matching nodes with complete proofs.", "lean_files": 91, "loc": 84864, "loc_code": 48810, "sorries": 39}]}